1
00:00:25,079 --> 00:00:27,599
Everything in this life has an end.

2
00:00:28,880 --> 00:00:33,599
Some people sit quietly and wait for that end to come to them.

3
00:00:35,079 --> 00:00:37,400
Some people get up and walk.

4
00:00:37,760 --> 00:00:39,840
He goes to the end on his own.

5
00:00:47,800 --> 00:00:49,760
I made a decision.

6
00:00:52,320 --> 00:00:54,880
Since I started this story,

7
00:00:55,760 --> 00:00:57,840
I will bring the end to it.

8
00:00:58,599 --> 00:01:00,639
This story is not another one,

9
00:01:01,199 --> 00:01:02,599
I will finish it.

10
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:16,480
Agah Beyoğlu…

11
00:01:19,559 --> 00:01:21,360
Tell me.

12
00:01:26,199 --> 00:01:28,360
Officer... I did it...

13
00:01:29,280 --> 00:01:31,519
All those people… I killed them.

14
00:01:32,599 --> 00:01:34,119
One by one…

15
00:01:34,960 --> 00:01:36,199
All…

16
00:04:14,679 --> 00:04:16,719
Do not do that! How many times have I told you!

17
00:04:16,840 --> 00:04:18,480
What the hell, he's having fun!

18
00:04:18,519 --> 00:04:21,199
Okay, but his blood pressure will rise.

19
00:04:27,800 --> 00:04:33,000
(unintelligible speech)

20
00:04:37,559 --> 00:04:40,800
Especially my wife will take care of her. Thank you.

21
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:43,639
I mean, it was the bathroom, the toilet, etc.

22
00:04:43,920 --> 00:04:45,079
He will always handle it.

23
00:04:45,280 --> 00:04:49,280
That's why we won't need an extra babysitter, thank you.

24
00:04:49,519 --> 00:04:51,639
Well, whatever you want.

25
00:04:51,920 --> 00:04:54,239
Well! Then if you sign your release papers…

26
00:04:54,400 --> 00:04:56,159
- Come on, let's go to my room. - Ok.

27
00:04:58,480 --> 00:05:01,280
When I first walked into that nursing home, I was faking it.

28
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:06,480
It was as if the disease had progressed and I had become disconnected from the world.

29
00:05:07,599 --> 00:05:11,000
The best place to hide after all those murders,

30
00:05:11,400 --> 00:05:13,719
It was a disease called Alzheimer's.

31
00:05:15,840 --> 00:05:18,639
But apparently the trick turned out to be real.

32
00:05:18,960 --> 00:05:22,559
I was trapped in my hiding place... I didn't know it.

33
00:05:24,079 --> 00:05:25,360
Baba!

34
00:05:26,119 --> 00:05:29,199
Father. Get up dad, come on, we're going home.

35
00:05:34,719 --> 00:05:35,480
Baba!

36
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:39,880
What happened?

37
00:05:41,360 --> 00:05:43,360
What's the part of this? Heh!

38
00:05:55,480 --> 00:05:57,599
What if, my dear, we could go to a hotel?

39
00:05:57,719 --> 00:06:01,599
As I said, it is very important for Ertan to be in an environment he knows.

40
00:06:01,760 --> 00:06:06,239
So there needs to be something around him that will jog his memory.

41
00:06:07,840 --> 00:06:12,239
Hah! Father! Isn't it my mother?

42
00:06:12,400 --> 00:06:14,599
Mebrure? Did you remember?

43
00:06:14,599 --> 00:06:17,280
How can the man remember? For God's sake!

44
00:06:17,880 --> 00:06:18,679
Father!

45
00:06:19,199 --> 00:06:20,079
Now look!

46
00:06:20,840 --> 00:06:23,280
You will drink this, okay?

47
00:06:23,559 --> 00:06:25,320
It'll all be over, let's see.

48
00:06:28,119 --> 00:06:33,199
Drink, drink, drink… Okay.

49
00:06:34,280 --> 00:06:35,239
Baba!

50
00:06:35,840 --> 00:06:38,639
You know, you left me at boarding school!

51
00:06:38,920 --> 00:06:40,440
I was so little!

52
00:06:40,800 --> 00:06:42,320
Do not worry about it!

53
00:06:42,639 --> 00:06:44,159
I won't leave you.

54
00:06:44,559 --> 00:06:45,599
Is it ok?

55
00:06:45,960 --> 00:06:48,159
Come on. Look at my mother!

56
00:06:48,320 --> 00:06:49,360
Saturn!

57
00:06:51,199 --> 00:06:52,239
Come on dad.

58
00:06:53,159 --> 00:06:54,199
What happened?

59
00:06:58,440 --> 00:07:01,840
My love, this man hasn't said a word for years.

60
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:05,079
He doesn't react to anything other than Tom Jones!

61
00:07:05,440 --> 00:07:09,800
Well! I don't understand how you think you will get better.

62
00:07:09,880 --> 00:07:12,760
No, now how did this biochemist give you this medicine!

63
00:07:13,199 --> 00:07:17,400
In other words, it is not even clear whether it is a medicine or not, it has not been tested, it has not been made, it has not been looked at!

64
00:07:17,480 --> 00:07:19,639
Maybe it has a side effect, don't you ever think about it?

65
00:07:22,639 --> 00:07:23,920
Where did it go?

66
00:07:24,360 --> 00:07:25,840
He is wandering around his house.

67
00:07:39,679 --> 00:07:40,800
DAY 1

68
00:08:10,280 --> 00:08:11,960
DAY 17

69
00:08:20,319 --> 00:08:20,840
Daddy!

70
00:08:45,159 --> 00:08:47,359
Have you ever come back from the dead?

71
00:08:52,319 --> 00:08:53,600
I'm back…

72
00:08:56,439 --> 00:08:57,680
But where did I turn?

73
00:08:58,840 --> 00:09:01,000
Turns out that was the real issue.

74
00:09:03,840 --> 00:09:05,800
Ok, I came back to life...

75
00:09:06,640 --> 00:09:09,640
Where exactly did I end up in that life?

76
00:09:11,960 --> 00:09:13,560
What did I do!

77
00:09:14,359 --> 00:09:16,319
I forgot to give water to Münir Bey!

78
00:09:16,680 --> 00:09:19,760
Mr. Munir! Where are you, my son Münir!

79
00:09:20,600 --> 00:09:22,920
Aah! Zuhal!

80
00:09:23,720 --> 00:09:26,119
No, what are you doing here? When did you come?

81
00:09:27,520 --> 00:09:29,159
Dad, do you know me?

82
00:09:29,239 --> 00:09:31,640
Do you know what it means? Are you kidding me girl?

83
00:09:31,760 --> 00:09:34,239
I'm looking for Münir Bey. Have you seen him? Tell him!

84
00:09:34,520 --> 00:09:36,479
Mr. Munir! There was a water container here!

85
00:09:36,600 --> 00:09:39,079
The child had a water bowl, but now he doesn't have a water bowl.

86
00:09:41,840 --> 00:09:43,640
Mr. Münir, where are you, son!

87
00:09:43,720 --> 00:09:45,159
Was this left in the bathroom?

88
00:09:45,560 --> 00:09:47,279
Don't let it be locked! Munir!

89
00:09:48,159 --> 00:09:50,520
- Thank God! Daddy! - Come on! Who is there!

90
00:09:50,520 --> 00:09:54,399
- Daddy! Do you remember me? - Who is there! Mr. Münir, did you stay there?

91
00:09:54,640 --> 00:09:57,520
Girl, what are you saying? What does it mean to remember!

92
00:09:57,760 --> 00:10:00,439
Well, it worked, huh! The medicine worked!

93
00:10:00,479 --> 00:10:01,239
Hayda!

94
00:10:01,319 --> 00:10:03,159
Ertan, my father knows me.

95
00:10:03,880 --> 00:10:04,880
What are you doing here?

96
00:10:04,880 --> 00:10:09,359
- He recognized you too! Thank God. - What's up, Ertan? You wouldn't come to your hometown!

97
00:10:10,439 --> 00:10:13,319
Wait a minute! How did you get in!

98
00:10:13,760 --> 00:10:15,359
Did you have the key too?

99
00:10:16,319 --> 00:10:17,479
Daddy!

100
00:10:17,640 --> 00:10:19,199
Girl, what happened, why are you crying?

101
00:10:20,359 --> 00:10:21,680
Did something happen to Deva?

102
00:10:22,960 --> 00:10:24,560
Deva, he said! Deva says!

103
00:10:24,600 --> 00:10:27,319
What should I say, should I say Mahmut? The child's name is Deva, right?

104
00:10:27,439 --> 00:10:30,159
Wait a minute, could you have left the door open? Ertan!

105
00:10:30,600 --> 00:10:32,680
Did you leave the door open and he ran away, Mr. Münir?

106
00:10:32,680 --> 00:10:35,680
- My daddy! - Look, if you did something like this. We change the cones accordingly!

107
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:39,199
Okay okay okay. Nothing, okay. Mr. Munir!

108
00:10:39,199 --> 00:10:42,359
That biochemist of yours will win the Nobel Prize, for sure!

109
00:10:42,359 --> 00:10:43,399
Mr. Munir!

110
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:46,359
Dad, do you really remember everything?

111
00:10:46,560 --> 00:10:47,000
My daughter!

112
00:10:47,119 --> 00:10:48,640
- When and what did I forget! - Heh!

113
00:10:48,920 --> 00:10:50,159
What was your surname, daddy?

114
00:10:50,279 --> 00:10:52,560
Are you kidding me, are you making fun of me, son?

115
00:10:52,720 --> 00:10:54,760
Is there any other Beyoğlu left in Beyoğlu other than me?

116
00:10:54,760 --> 00:10:59,600
- Mr. Munir! Mr. Munir! Where is this kid? - This is a miracle, I swear it is a miracle.

117
00:10:59,640 --> 00:11:01,399
- Dad! Let me ask you something too.. - Mr. Münir!

118
00:11:01,520 --> 00:11:02,800
- What? - Dad, what were you doing?

119
00:11:02,920 --> 00:11:06,840
- Where did you retire from? - Girl, for God's sake, go and find another entertainment for yourself.

120
00:11:06,880 --> 00:11:09,600
What were you doing, Daddy? Where did you retire from?

121
00:11:09,720 --> 00:11:12,479
Grandmother ? How where? Say well!

122
00:11:12,560 --> 00:11:13,640
Where is dad?

123
00:11:14,239 --> 00:11:15,880
Well, I was doing something!

124
00:11:16,640 --> 00:11:17,800
What were you doing?

125
00:11:22,600 --> 00:11:24,319
Well, I was doing something!

126
00:11:30,079 --> 00:11:31,600
Courthouse clerk?

127
00:11:36,119 --> 00:11:38,880
I studied law, what's the point!

128
00:11:39,800 --> 00:11:44,319
You haven't finished university, daddy. You left when you married my mother.

129
00:11:45,279 --> 00:11:47,000
How many years did you say?

130
00:11:47,319 --> 00:11:48,359
Twenty seven.

131
00:11:48,920 --> 00:11:54,000
Twenty-seven years! Was I a courthouse clerk for twenty-seven years?

132
00:11:54,720 --> 00:11:58,239
There is no such thing, there is something wrong. No such thing!

133
00:11:58,520 --> 00:11:58,960
Baba!

134
00:11:59,000 --> 00:11:59,399
Heh!

135
00:11:59,520 --> 00:12:02,520
Look! Look now, look at this photo.

136
00:12:02,640 --> 00:12:05,159
Look, this is the Ardıçhan courthouse.

137
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:06,479
Is it ok?

138
00:12:06,479 --> 00:12:08,359
Look, you know what's here?

139
00:12:08,720 --> 00:12:11,760
Look, for example, these photos were taken in Silopi.

140
00:12:12,119 --> 00:12:17,600
Look who's around you? All your friends and colleagues from the courthouse.

141
00:12:20,600 --> 00:12:25,520
Now you tell me that I have spent my entire life in civil service,

142
00:12:25,520 --> 00:12:26,600
That's what you're telling me!

143
00:12:26,720 --> 00:12:29,439
No, daddy, it's not like that, but you were very happy,

144
00:12:29,439 --> 00:12:31,520
- So you loved what you did. - How do you know?

145
00:12:31,520 --> 00:12:34,399
Heh!. How do you know I'm happy?

146
00:12:34,760 --> 00:12:36,640
I mean, you looked like that, daddy.

147
00:12:36,920 --> 00:12:38,560
So I was deceiving myself!

148
00:12:40,199 --> 00:12:43,520
Dad, look at it this way, you're getting angry, annoyed, etc.

149
00:12:43,840 --> 00:12:45,239
What else would you do?

150
00:12:45,439 --> 00:12:47,640
I don't know, girl! I don't know what I was going to do!

151
00:12:47,960 --> 00:12:51,319
I don't know! I don't remember! Who was I, what was I, what was I doing!

152
00:12:52,520 --> 00:12:53,239
No way!

153
00:12:53,720 --> 00:12:55,319
First of all, I am a poet-spirited man!

154
00:12:55,479 --> 00:12:56,439
Is he a poet?

155
00:12:57,119 --> 00:12:59,520
''I am a walnut tree in Gülhane park''

156
00:12:59,880 --> 00:13:02,760
''Neither you nor the police are aware of this.''

157
00:13:04,079 --> 00:13:07,640
If I were not a poet, how would I remember Nazım Hikmet? Heh?

158
00:13:07,920 --> 00:13:09,600
I don't even remember what I do yet.

159
00:13:09,840 --> 00:13:12,760
Daddy, please don't do such things, take care of yourself!

160
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:16,319
Until yesterday, you didn't remember who we were.

161
00:13:16,479 --> 00:13:20,079
Would you look at yourself now? Please! Poems, poems.

162
00:13:20,319 --> 00:13:24,680
Aah, you are the only person in this world who had Alzheimer's and recovered.

163
00:13:24,880 --> 00:13:26,119
Think about this, I ask!

164
00:13:26,159 --> 00:13:29,840
I got better, but what happened? No, what happened now, I knew, I learned, what happened?

165
00:13:30,239 --> 00:13:31,439
If you had left me like that.

166
00:13:31,800 --> 00:13:34,479
Look, please don't say that, dad, I really feel sorry for you.

167
00:13:34,760 --> 00:13:37,079
Mr. Münir is not there anyway! What did you do to the cat?

168
00:13:37,800 --> 00:13:38,760
Where is this cat?

169
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:41,800
Dad, there is no cat!

170
00:13:41,920 --> 00:13:43,880
What do you mean, how can it not exist?

171
00:13:44,399 --> 00:13:45,520
Let me die so I can be saved!

172
00:13:45,680 --> 00:13:47,199
What kind of world is this, what kind of life is this?

173
00:13:47,600 --> 00:13:49,720
Münir Bey is not there either! Let me die and be saved!

174
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:05,600
Daddy!

175
00:14:06,319 --> 00:14:07,720
He lost consciousness.

176
00:14:07,960 --> 00:14:10,560
Daddy! Father!

177
00:14:10,920 --> 00:14:12,680
- He shut down, he shut down, his consciousness turned off. - Daddy!

178
00:14:20,439 --> 00:14:24,840
Dad, daddy. Dad, are you okay?

179
00:14:37,079 --> 00:14:39,960
You were already going to kill yourself.

180
00:14:42,239 --> 00:14:44,560
Who knows how unhappy you were.

181
00:14:46,920 --> 00:14:48,600
If only you had squeezed your head!

182
00:14:50,159 --> 00:14:51,760
You couldn't do it, could you?

183
00:14:53,560 --> 00:14:55,199
Because you were afraid.

184
00:14:56,439 --> 00:14:57,520
You were afraid of death.

185
00:14:57,600 --> 00:14:58,640
(laugh)

186
00:14:59,319 --> 00:15:01,079
You coward!

187
00:15:04,880 --> 00:15:08,399
You must also be afraid of being hungry! Ass!

188
00:15:08,720 --> 00:15:11,399
That's why you went and became a clerk, right?

189
00:15:15,479 --> 00:15:17,399
But I'm not afraid!

190
00:15:19,199 --> 00:15:20,840
Do you know why?

191
00:15:22,560 --> 00:15:25,399
Because I am Agah Beyoğlu.

192
00:15:31,600 --> 00:15:33,560
I have to leave immediately. I have a job.

193
00:15:33,600 --> 00:15:34,520
Where to dad?

194
00:15:34,640 --> 00:15:36,199
I'm going to do something I've never done before!

195
00:15:36,600 --> 00:15:37,399
What is it?

196
00:15:37,479 --> 00:15:38,680
I will live my life!

197
00:15:38,960 --> 00:15:40,640
What will you do? How will you live your life?

198
00:15:40,760 --> 00:15:41,880
I have two questions for you.

199
00:15:42,239 --> 00:15:44,359
One! Where's your mother's car?

200
00:15:44,600 --> 00:15:47,359
Two! Which donkey made me wear these!

201
00:15:59,319 --> 00:16:02,760
Who are you? Who are you?

202
00:16:02,800 --> 00:16:04,960
- Oh dad, it's so beautiful. - So sweet.

203
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:06,079
AGAIN

204
00:16:40,479 --> 00:16:44,439
Father! Oh dad! Ugh!

205
00:16:44,439 --> 00:16:46,359
Father! Wait!

206
00:16:46,359 --> 00:16:49,800
- Oh Ertan, why don't you stop it? - I'm paying for it, Zuhal!

207
00:16:49,840 --> 00:16:51,600
(laugh)

208
00:16:51,920 --> 00:16:58,640
(nida)

209
00:17:04,319 --> 00:17:11,000
(unintelligible speech)

210
00:17:28,359 --> 00:17:35,720
(enthusiastic voices)

211
00:17:42,880 --> 00:17:49,520
(enthusiastic voices)

212
00:18:00,520 --> 00:18:07,399
(enthusiastic voices)

213
00:19:21,359 --> 00:19:22,520
- Ahhh!

214
00:19:22,520 --> 00:19:27,159
(unintelligible speech)

215
00:19:46,600 --> 00:19:50,479
(unintelligible speech)

216
00:19:53,840 --> 00:19:55,399
Brother, don't do it!

217
00:19:55,399 --> 00:19:59,920
(unintelligible speech)

218
00:19:59,920 --> 00:20:02,640
Ahhh! Ahhh! Ahhh!

219
00:20:02,640 --> 00:20:05,439
(unintelligible speech)

220
00:20:05,439 --> 00:20:07,720
Ahhh!

221
00:20:09,159 --> 00:20:12,600
Officer! Officer! Officer!

222
00:20:13,000 --> 00:20:14,119
- Are you okay, uncle!

223
00:20:14,640 --> 00:20:15,600
I killed a man!

224
00:20:15,640 --> 00:20:16,600
What do you say, uncle?

225
00:20:17,159 --> 00:20:18,119
I killed so many people!

226
00:20:19,840 --> 00:20:22,800
I say murderer! I'm a killer!

227
00:20:26,159 --> 00:20:28,600
Chief, take a look, this says something.

228
00:20:29,920 --> 00:20:31,119
Did something happen, uncle?

229
00:20:31,159 --> 00:20:36,359
(Mumbling)

230
00:20:41,880 --> 00:20:43,640
Well, you don't have a criminal record either, uncle.

231
00:20:43,800 --> 00:20:46,199
But I'm just telling you, I hit that much, I say!

232
00:20:46,560 --> 00:20:47,840
Why don't you believe me?

233
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:50,399
Okay uncle, okay, he will come now, you can tell him.

234
00:20:50,640 --> 00:20:51,600
Who will come?

235
00:20:55,560 --> 00:20:56,840
Come on, Mr. Prosecutor.

236
00:20:57,199 --> 00:20:57,840
You go out.

237
00:21:06,159 --> 00:21:08,960
- Now you remember that you shot someone. -Yes.

238
00:21:09,960 --> 00:21:11,680
But you don't know who you are, do you?

239
00:21:11,800 --> 00:21:12,920
No, I don't remember.

240
00:21:14,000 --> 00:21:15,800
Why did you shoot these people, do you remember that?

241
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:17,119
No, I don't remember that either.

242
00:21:17,800 --> 00:21:21,640
Ah! I! I forgot something!

243
00:21:21,760 --> 00:21:22,279
What?

244
00:21:22,439 --> 00:21:23,359
Is there any head left?

245
00:21:23,520 --> 00:21:24,800
Am the Alzheimer var.

246
00:21:25,399 --> 00:21:27,119
That's why I don't remember.

247
00:21:27,640 --> 00:21:29,520
- Alzheimer's? - Yes!

248
00:21:31,640 --> 00:21:33,079
Oh my God!

249
00:21:39,600 --> 00:21:40,640
Understood, uncle.

250
00:21:40,960 --> 00:21:43,600
Well, but wait a minute! I remember their faces!

251
00:21:43,840 --> 00:21:45,640
I remember where I hit!

252
00:21:45,800 --> 00:21:48,800
Even what did I tell them, what did they say to me...

253
00:21:48,960 --> 00:21:50,439
I remember all of these.

254
00:21:50,520 --> 00:21:51,560
For example, let me tell you this.

255
00:21:52,760 --> 00:21:57,359
Well, for example, we are in a narrow street at night.

256
00:21:58,439 --> 00:21:59,600
For example, that's Beyoğlu for sure.

257
00:21:59,600 --> 00:22:03,399
I guess it's one of the back streets of Istiklal Avenue or something.

258
00:22:03,760 --> 00:22:06,800
